XueModules

Giuliano Netto Flores Cruz

September 20, 2018

Modules from Xue, 2014.

9498 unique present genes were clustered into 49 modules. M1-, M2- and TPP-associated modules are 7-9, 13-15, and 30, 32-33, respecitively.

List of Genes used for the 49 modules defined by Xue, 2014. Human gene symbols were converted to the respective mouse orthologues by combining information from Ensembl BioMart ( http://www.ensembl.org/biomart/martview ) using the species specific gene symbols and Ensembl Gene IDs.. For some of the genes BioGPS (http://biogps.org/#goto=welcome) was used if no orthologue was found in BioMart

uq_elem=c()
for(i in 1:ncol(dat))
{
  uq_elem=c(unique(dat[,i]), uq_elem)
  uq_elem=unique(uq_elem)
}
genes_list <- data.frame('GeneSymbols' =uq_elem)

datatable(genes_list, filter = 'top',
          caption = "Table 2. Genes included in modules by Xue, 2014.",
          options=list(pageLength = 100, scrollX='400px', scrollY='400px',
          lengthMenu = c(30, 100, 1000)))
